    b = [int(x) for x in input().split()]
    m = int(input())
    dp = [[0 for i in range(m+1)] for j in range(n+1)]
    dp[0][0] = 1
    for i in range(1, n+1):
        for j in range(m+1):
            dp[i][j] = dp[i-1][j]
            if j >= a[i-1]:
                dp[i][j] += dp[i][j-a[i-1]]
    print(dp[n][m] % 1000000007)

# Get input
    n, k, q = [int(x) for x in input().split()]
    arr = [int(x) for x in input().split()]
    # Initialize variables
    min_val = arr[0]
    max_val = arr[0]
    # Loop through the Q operations
    for i in range(q):
        # Find the minimum and maximum values in the array
        for j in range(k):
            if arr[j] < min_val:
                min_val = arr[j]
            if arr[j] > max_val:
                max_val = arr[j]
        # Remove the minimum value
        arr.remove(min_val)
        # Update the minimum and maximum values
        if arr[0] < min_val:
            min_val = arr[0]
        if arr[-1] > max_val:
            max_val = arr[-1]
    # Print the difference between the largest and smallest values
    print(max_val - min_val)
